My team relies heavily on feature specific JIRA filters on our confluence page. They are an amazing way for us to see the remaining ticket in a project.

The one thing that is missing is the ability to show a total for the time fields (or story points if you use those). Our PMs end up copying the data into a spread sheet or using a sum equation in a JIRA search so that they can see the total remaining time.

It would be very helpful to be able to see a total at the bottom.

From a recent ticket provided in the comments section, we have found out that not having protocol inside the server.xml causes synchrony to fail.

Therefore, it's great if we include a reminder in the documentation that having the protocol is important for the success of Collaborative Editing.

{code}
protocol="org.apache.coyote.http11.Http11NioProtocol
{code}

